-->

<p>
Select Applications&rarr;Ubuntu Software Center.
<ul>
  <li> g++: The GNU C++ compiler.
  <li> python-wxversion: wxWidgets cross-platform C++ GUI toolkit.
  <li> python-matplotlib: Python based plotting system in style
  similar to Matlab.
  <li> python-scipy: Scientific Tools for Python.
  <li> python-sympy: Computer Algebra System (CAS) in Python.
</ul>
Then follow the <a href="InstallationLinux.htm">installation instructions</a>
to compile the solvers and launch the application.
</p>

